summary: Catalina Torres lives and works between Barcelona, ​​The Hague and Montevideo. She graduated from the Andy Goldstein School of Creative Photography in 2019. She studied Documentary Film at the National University of San Martín, in Buenos Aires. She is currently selected to participate in the MA Photography & Society at the Royal Academy of art The Hague. His work has been exhibited in collective and individual exhibitions. For more than five years she has been doing commercial work as a photographer, audiovisual producer, video editor and creative director.
